==English==
===Etymology===
From {{F.}} ''[[sanguin]]'', ultimately from {{L.}} ''[[sanguineus]]''.
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-sanguine.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''sanguine'''
# (colour) Blood [[color]]; [[red]].
#:<table><tr><td>sanguine colour: &nbsp;</td><td bgcolor="#BC3F4A" width="80">&nbsp; </td></tr></table>
# Anything of a [[blood]]-red color, as [[cloth]].
# [[bloodstone|Bloodstone]].
# Red [[crayon]]. See the Note under [[Crayon]], 1.

===Verb===
'''to sanguine'''
# To [[stain]] with blood; to impart the color of blood to; to ensanguine.

===Adjective===
'''sanguine'''
#(colour) Having the color of blood; red.
# Characterized by [[abundance]] and active [[circulation]] of blood.
#:''a '''sanguine''' bodily temperament''
# Warm; [[ardent]].
#:''a '''sanguine''' temper''
# Anticipating the best; not [[desponding]]; [[confident]]; full of [[hope]]
#:'''''sanguine''' of success''
#(''Obsolete''): [[irresponsibly]] [[mirthful]]; [[indulgent]] in [[pleasure]] to the [[exclusion]] of [[important]] matters
#*'''1592''' — [[Shakespeare]], ''[http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Tragedy_of_Titus_Andronicus Titus Andronicus] iv 2''
#*:What, what, ye '''sanguine''', shallow-hearted boys!
#*'''1597''' — [[Shakespeare]], ''[http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_First_Part_of_King_Henry_the_Fourth 1 Hen IV] ii 4''
#*:I'll be no longer guilty of this sin; this '''sanguine''' coward, this
#*:bed-presser, this horse-back-breaker, this huge hill of flesh.

====Usage note====
Not to be confused with [[sanguinary]].  ''Sanguine'' means 'optimistic', ''sanguinary'' means 'blood-thirsty, gory'.

